{
  "texts": [
    "During the empirical study, we take the best-performing LLM (i.e., GPT-3.5) as an example and carry out the in-depth analysis based on a series of failed cases sampled from GPT-3.5's results, thereby exploring potential improvement directions for LLMs in code translation.",
    "Specifically, to ensure a 95% confidence level and 5% confidence interval when sampling, we follow previous work [15,26,57,64] to randomly sample a total of 195 failed casesfoot_3 from GPT-3.5's empirical results, where 52 are from C++ to Python, 43 are from Python to C++, 30 are from Java to C++, and 70 are from C++ to Java.",
    "Particularly, 21 cases extracted from the dataset of C++ to Java are ignored, as their mistakes are owing to the misintroduction of \"import\" statements or wrapped by \"class\", which can be easily eliminated by regular expressions.",
    "Eventually, 174 failed cases remained.",
    "Subsequently, we made a systematic taxonomy according to the cause of each failure."
  ]
}